Hi 🙋🏻‍♀️ 
I haven’t posted in a while. I was busy without anything to show, cause I’m working on color layers for the large Mardi Gras print. It’s gonna be ready to show next week. Meanwhile check my story for progress. 
I also have a Little commission coming up next week and the week after I’m leaving to New Orleans. That means the online shop will be closed from January 22nd until I get back in mid March. 
Those are the news! 🙃

I’ve been drafting on a large piece for a bit. This one will be titled „Chef“ and it’s gonna be a full color print. Block size will be 70x100cm 😁 Can’t wait to get this on the block tomorrow! The draft is on transparent paper and there are a few layers, as you can see. I will need those again later for prepping the color blocks. So much planning! 🙃 so much fun!

I’m hosting an open house this Friday and Saturday May 12.&13. at my studio as part of the Meidlinger Atelier Rundgang. Please come by and see some of my work, as well as my work in progress on the new block “Chef”. A lot of other artists from my building are showing work too. Studios at KQM are open 13:30-19:30. We are at Aichholzgasse 51-53, 1120 Wien. My studio is room 20, in the very back of the ground floor. Follow the pink line to find me!!
.
.
